habendum.d:
n. That part of a deed which follows the part called the
   premises, and determines the extent of the interest or estate granted;
   -- so called because it begins with the word Habendum.

halidom.d:
n. Holiness; sanctity; sacred oath; sacred things; sanctuary;
   -- used chiefly in oaths.
n. Holy doom; the Last Day.

haloed.d:
imp. & p. p. of Halo
a. Surrounded with a halo; invested with an ideal glory;
   glorified.
